oakcurric:unit-3848
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: an introduction to dance"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-an-introduction-to-dance" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will challenge pupils to respond to the changing stimuli using a
  range of different and controlled actions, showing character, expression, control and
  accuracy. Pupils will learn how to co-ordinate their bodies to create short sequences."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the key knowledge essential for dance. Pupils
  will further develop their motor competence to complement their physical education experience
  in other aspects of PE, whilst introducing opportunities to be expressive and respond to
  creative stimuli such as music. Skills learnt within this unit will be developed, extended
  and build upon the foundational movement skills and creative play introduced through the EYFS
  curriculum.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3848-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3848-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3848-3 ;
  curric:id "3848"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.886976Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 .

oakcurric:unit-3845
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: locomotion"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-locomotion" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will increase pupils’ motor competence when running and jumping. Pupils
  will show self-belief as they explore different ways of moving and balancing, and linking
  these together."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The unit introduces pupils to locomotion skills that can be developed and
  applied in a wide range of upcoming units. Building on their foundational movement skills
  from early years, pupils will develop motor competence when learning how to run and jump.
  This progresses into the application of these skills when creating short sequences, as well
  as exploring balancing. This learning equips pupils with the knowledge to understand how,
  where and why we move, before combining this understanding with other curriculum areas.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3845-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3845-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3845-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3845-4 ;
  curric:id "3845"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.925557Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 .

oakcurric:unit-3846
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Remote learning: an introduction to target games"@en ;
  curric:slug "home-learning-an-introduction-to-target-games" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit of work will develop pupils' ability to accurately send a ball towards a
  target. Pupils will learn and apply their developing knowledge of where we send a ball and
  why, in order to score points to beat an opponent."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit will introduce pupils to the skills and understanding required
  to send an object accurately. The unit will introduce pupils to rolling and throwing
  accurately towards a target, so that these skills can then be applied later on in simple
  games activities. The introduction to the importance of sending accurately will ensure that
  pupils begin to grasp simple concepts for attacking successfully in games.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3846-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3846-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3846-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3846-4 ;
  curric:id "3846"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.992584Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 .

oakcurric:unit-2963
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: individual movements and balances"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-individual-movements-and-balances" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will introduce pupils to creating movements and balances whilst
  developing movement competence. Pupils will explore moving and balancing in high, low,
  wide, narrow and curled ways, on the floor and on apparatus. Pupils will add movements
  together and reflect on their ideas."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit will build on the movement competence that will have taken place
  in their initial locomotion and dance units. Pupils will start to create movements and
  balances through gymnastics and be challenged to focus on the quality of each movement and to
  start to sequence these movements together. This unit will also introduce pupils to the idea
  of working together safely as they navigate the apparatus set up, being responsible for
  themselves and others, which is developed further in Year 2. This unit will give pupils the
  confidence to give self-and peer feedback in future units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2963-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2963-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2963-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2963-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2963-5 ;
  curric:id "2963"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.922630Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection .

oakcurric:unit-2962
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: working with others"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-working-with-others" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will explore how to work with a partner and then within a team. Pupils
  will learn the importance of turn taking, fair play, following rules, and how to adjust a
  game so that everyone feels they can succeed and have fun."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit will provide an excellent opportunity for pupils to apply the
  skills they have begun to develop in the locomotion, gymnastics, and ball skills units. It
  will enable pupils to develop their ability to work with others, as well as developing their
  communication skills. Pupils will go on to understand the importance of empathy and fair
  play. This unit will provide the foundational knowledge required to develop a sense of
  teamwork and learn how to problem solve collectively.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2962-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2962-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2962-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2962-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2962-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2962-6 ;
  curric:id "2962"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.925016Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

oakcurric:unit-2971
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Outdoor adventurous activities: team building"@en ;
  curric:slug "outdoor-adventurous-activities-team-building" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will develop pupils’ ability to apply effective teamwork, ensuring that
  everyone is included and understands their role. Pupils will begin to develop and apply
  simple strategies to solve problems with a focus on applying effective collaboration
  skills when working as part of a team."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils have already experienced working together and know why we need to
  collaborate to beat an opponent. Pupils have developed an understanding of using simple
  tactics in games. Through this unit they will deepen their understanding of creating tactics
  and applying these in games. By challenging collaboration skills, pupils will gain a deeper
  understanding and appreciation for their teammates; preparing them for every aspect of their
  future learning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2971-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2971-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2971-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2971-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2971-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2971-6 ;
  curric:id "2971"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.008717Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-decision-making-problem-solving-and-creative-thinking .

oakcurric:unit-2965
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dance: my moves, my brilliant body"@en ;
  curric:slug "dance-my-moves-my-brilliant-body" ;
  rdfs:comment """A pure approach introduces Action-Space-Dynamics-Relationships and some
  constituent elements in each as a basis for future units. Pupils combine content making
  personal choices based on problem-solving, aesthetics and safety, providing opportunities
  to reflect and share opinions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will already know the key knowledge essential for dance alongside
  opportunities to connect physical, linguistic and cognitive learning. Pupils will further
  develop their motor competence to complement their physical education experience in other
  aspects of PE whilst introducing opportunities to be expressive and respond to creative
  stimuli such as music. Skills learnt within this unit will be developed, extended and built
  upon the foundational movement skills and creative play introduced through the EYFS
  curriculum.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2965-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2965-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2965-3 ;
  curric:id "2965"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.178233Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-2961
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Ball skills: sending, receiving and dribbling"@en ;
  curric:slug "ball-skills-sending-receiving-and-dribbling" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will explore and develop pupils’ movement competence when sending and
  receiving a ball. They will develop and apply an understanding of how, where and why we
  send a ball, stop the ball and dribble the ball using our hands and feet effectively.
  Pupils will also explore working in teams."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This will be the first unit using balls that pupils experience. The unit
  will introduce pupils to the movement skills and understanding required to send and receive
  accurately so that these skills can then be applied later on in simple activities. The
  introduction to dribbling will expand upon pupil’s prior learning of moving into a space as
  they begin to move into space with a ball. Pupils will develop an understanding of how to
  apply these skills in simple games later in the unit, providing them with a basis to continue
  to develop teamwork and leadership skills in the future.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2961-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2961-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2961-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2961-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2961-5 ;
  curric:id "2961"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.210685Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-2972
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Gymnastics: linking movements and balances"@en ;
  curric:slug "gymnastics-linking-movements-and-balances" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils to explore linking movements and balances together
  incorporating flow. Pupils will create and perform sequences on apparatus focussing on
  jumps, rolls and balances. Pupils will reflect on how to link movements and balances while
  travelling along a variety of pathways."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit continues to develop pupil’s knowledge and application of
  creating movements and balances, covered previously. Pupils will build upon and further
  develop their ability to sequence movements together by including effective flow. Pupils will
  be challenged to explore additional compositional components such as pathways and learn to
  execute their movements sequences while considering a variety of pathways. The unit will
  fully prepare pupils for the next steps in sequence design which will include pair and group
  work.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2972-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2972-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2972-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2972-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2972-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2972-6 ;
  curric:id "2972"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.271618Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-think-evaluation-analysis-and-reflection ,
    oakcurric:thread-move-performance-and-competition .

oakcurric:unit-2975
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: agility, balance and coordination"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-agility-balance-and-coordination" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit of work will introduce pupils to agility, balance and coordination;
  understanding what they mean and why they are important. Pupils will perform circuits to
  develop their application and understanding of how these elements are crucial in a variety
  of fitness activities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils’ prior understanding of exercise, physical
  activity and why we need to move our bodies. By exploring agility, balance and coordination,
  throughout the unit, pupils will further develop their ability to understand the effects
  exercise has on our bodies. Later in the unit pupils will begin to apply their agility,
  balance and coordination through circuits and games, where they will be honest with their
  scores as they strive to improve their own performance and physical fitness. This will
  prepare pupils for all upcoming practical units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2975-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2975-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2975-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2975-4 ;
  curric:id "2975"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.273521Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-2960
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Locomotion: running and jumping"@en ;
  curric:slug "locomotion-running-and-jumping" ;
  rdfs:comment """The unit will increase pupils’ motor competence when running, providing an
  understanding of where we run and why. Pupils will show self belief, exploring jumping in
  different directions, at different speeds, heights and distances. Pupils will learn how
  and why we jump with the correct technique."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This is the first unit that pupils experience in year 1. The unit
  introduces pupils to locomotion skills that can be developed and applied in a wide range of
  upcoming units. Building on their foundational movement skills from early years, pupils will
  develop motor competence when learning how to run and jump. This progresses into the
  application of these skills in games and through the athletic lens of running fast and
  jumping far. This learning equips pupils with the knowledge to understand where we move and
  why, before combining this understanding with a ball or in gymnastics and dance.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2960-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2960-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2960-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2960-4 ;
  curric:id "2960"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.275721Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-personal-and-emotional .

oakcurric:unit-2964
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dance: my moves, my journeys"@en ;
  curric:slug "dance-my-moves-my-journeys" ;
  rdfs:comment """A narrative approach consolidates core learning of
  Action-Space-Dynamics-Relationships and introduces elements to expand dance knowledge.
  Pupils combine making artistic decisions by responding to creative tasks. When performing,
  pupils reflect, analyse and share ideas using simple terminology."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The unit will reinforce key subject knowledge from prior learning, through
  narrative methodologies enabling pupils to imagine, create, interpret as well as connect
  physical, linguistic and cognitive learning from other curriculum areas. Pupils will continue
  to develop motor competence to complement their wider physical education experience whilst
  introducing opportunities to be expressive and respond to creative stimuli such as the spoken
  word and music. Later in this unit pupils will develop, extend and build upon the
  foundational movement teaching and creative play.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2964-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2964-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2964-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2964-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2964-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2964-6 ;
  curric:id "2964"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.362404Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-cultural-and-ethical-awareness .

oakcurric:unit-2968
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Locomotion: running, jumping and dodging"@en ;
  curric:slug "locomotion-running-jumping-and-dodging" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will increase pupils’ motor competence when dodging and jumping. Pupils
  will understand when and why we dodge and apply this knowledge showing self belief in
  simple games. Pupils will use their jumping skills in games too and use this understanding
  to jump in combination by linking jumps."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """The unit will use pupils’ prior knowledge of how to run and jump,
  developing pupils' motor competence linked to dodging and jumping. In this unit pupils will
  be challenged to use and apply dodging skills in games and jump in combination rather than
  just in isolation. Pupils will also be able to use their prior learning from ball skills and
  team games to be able to successfully apply their initial jumping and dodging skills in this
  unit. Foundations are then laid for subsequent units on ball skills as pupils will already
  have a strong understanding of the movement skills required.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2968-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2968-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2968-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2968-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2968-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2968-6 ;
  curric:id "2968"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.365039Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-feel-engagement-and-enjoyment .

oakcurric:unit-2974
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Dance: my world, how we dance"@en ;
  curric:slug "dance-my-world-how-we-dance" ;
  rdfs:comment """A stylistic approach applies Action-Space-Dynamics-Relationships in combination to
  cultural, historic and geographic factors. Pupils learn key features of different dance
  genres e.g. stance and formations as a stimulus for devising motifs and developing
  awareness of commonality between cultures."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils are introduced to new actions through dances from other times and
  places. Applying subject knowledge as an analytical tool to encode and decode established
  vocabularies and support cultural appreciation. This develops musicality and relationship as
  well as developing coordination, sensitivity to others and projection skills. Collaborating
  in small groups, pupils discuss ideas; select, order or combine them; review success and
  consider refinements prior to sharing and observing work, offering further analysis.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2974-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2974-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2974-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2974-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2974-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2974-6 ;
  curric:id "2974"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.412322Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-application-of-tactics-strategies-and-compositional-ideas ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership .

oakcurric:unit-2969
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Ball skills: passing, dribbling and scoring"@en ;
  curric:slug "ball-skills-passing-dribbling-and-scoring" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will challenge pupils to use their dribbling, passing and receiving
  skills to keep possession and score. Pupils will develop their accurate underarm throwing
  and explore throwing overarm. Pupils will apply these skills in a variety of activities as
  they develop their motor competence."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit of work will develop pupils' motor competence of moving with a
  ball using their hands and feet, while introducing pupils to more advanced skills such as
  throwing over arm. This unit is essential in order to fully prepare pupils for the
  application of their ball skills in more advanced games. The introduction of scoring in this
  unit will also embed more complex skills and rules which are necessary for pupils to access
  the following games units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2969-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2969-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2969-3 ,
