  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-movement-competence ,
    oakcurric:thread-connect-teamwork-and-leadership .

oakcurric:unit-2966
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Health and wellbeing: the effects of exercise"@en ;
  curric:slug "health-and-wellbeing-the-effects-of-exercise" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit will teach pupils to identify changes in their heartbeat and breathing
  when they exercise. Pupils will begin to understand how exercise makes them feel both
  physically and mentally. Pupils will develop their knowledge of the positive impact
  exercise has on our bodies and lifestyles."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """During their locomotion unit, pupils may have experienced the effects of
  exercise, but this unit is the first time pupils will be challenged to think about why we
  move and how important movement is for our bodies. Introducing words such as exercise and
  wellbeing will teach pupils to the different ways we can exercise through PE and physical
  activity. The unit will prepare pupils for all future learning through PE and encourage
  pupils to have a positive experience of movement as they start their journeys to
  understanding the impact exercise has on leading healthy, active lifestyles.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2966-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2966-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2966-3 ;
  curric:id "2966"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:25.786909Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-physical-education-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-move-physical-fitness ,
    oakcurric:thread-think-knowledge-of-healthy-active-living .

